The Supreme Court has ordered the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) to issue a certificate of return to the governorship candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in Bayelsa State, Diri Duoye. This decision was reached after a unanimous decision by a five-man panel of Justices led by Justice Mary Odili sacked the governor-elect of Bayelsa State, David Lyon and his Deputy, Biobarakuma Degi-Eremieoyo. David Lyon was sacked for presenting a running mate with a fake certificate in the just concluded Bayelsa State Governorship election. Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook 